  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a simple studio with a mottled gray wall and floor. A pale silver four-door sedan is seen in clean side profile, with an adult man in a dark suit, white shirt, and tie standing behind it near the driver’s side. A black hook hangs from above, centered over the car, suggesting a staged product reveal. The hook lifts what looks like a silvery car-shaped covering or shell. As it rises, the silver body folds upward into a tent-like shape, revealing a glossy red Buick sedan underneath. The man remains beside the car, watching the reveal.\n\nThe red LeSabre is then shown from the front at an angle, its shiny hood, black grille, rectangular headlights, and chrome-accented bumper facing forward. The suited presenter stands to the left of the car, looking upward as the lifted silver covering is carried away above him. White on-screen text appears at the upper right reading “3800 V6,” while the red sedan remains displayed prominently in the studio.\n\nThe view shifts inside the car, showing a roomy gray interior with broad, padded seats. The rear bench and front seats have horizontal stitched sections and a soft leather-like finish. Seat belts hang neatly between the seats, and the passenger-side door panel includes a strip of woodgrain trim. As the view moves across the cabin toward the driver’s area, the steering wheel and dashboard come into view on the right. White text at the lower right reads “Driver Air Bag,” identifying the safety feature being highlighted.\n\nNext, the rear of the red LeSabre is shown with its trunk open. The suited man leans in from the left, holding a large light-colored suitcase with both hands. He slides the suitcase into the dark trunk opening without having to lift it very high. White text at the bottom reads “Low-Liftover Trunk.” The suitcase settles flat inside, and the man steps back. He then lowers the trunk lid. As it closes, the rear of the car fills the view: wide red taillights stretch across the back, a license plate reads “LESABRE,” and a “BUICK” badge appears on the right side of the trunk area. The “Low-Liftover Trunk” text remains at the bottom during this demonstration.\n\nThe red sedan returns to the gray studio setting from the rear three-quarter angle. The presenter stands to the left of the car and reaches upward toward a hanging line or handle. A large gray backdrop begins to lift like a curtain, revealing a bright outdoor road scene behind it. As the wall rises, a sunlit, landscaped street appears, bordered by green grass, shrubs, trees, and a curving curb. The red LeSabre is positioned as if ready to drive out of the studio and onto the road.\n\nThe presenter steps aside, and the red sedan drives forward away from the studio area onto the winding residential-looking road. It moves farther into the distance, centered on the lane, with lush greenery and trees framing the scene. Near the end, large red “BUICK” text appears over the lower center of the picture, with black text below reading “The New Symbol For Quality In America.” A phone number, “1-800-531-1115,” appears beneath the slogan while the red LeSabre continues along the curving road in the background.",
